So something that’s pretty cool is that a lot of the flaws you mentioned were intentional and used for character development. I actually forgot a lot of the first episode. Yeah, Rebecca is crazy, as in, she has a legitimate mental illness that lets her justify all of her creepy stalker behavior until it falls apart around her. Yes, Paula has way too much free time and is way too invested in the love story, and this later causes problems in her marriage and she ends up becoming more crazy than Rebecca in some scenes.

It’s like taking the tropes of a rom com and showing how destructive these behaviors are in real life.

snippet.textDisplay: I personally love this show so so much. I’m so sad it’s over. It’s such a powerful show and held such a special place in my heart. I was diagnosed with cancer the year it came out. I was struggling so much with my body image and dealing with depression and anxiety. Considering how much I love musicals, this show really helped me out if a dark place. It helped me realize that anxiety and depression is okay, and helped me laugh through my experience. If anyone hasn’t seen it, you really should. It’s funny and relatable and I wish it had more seasons. Thanks to Rachel Bloom for this show ❤️
